race.comment: TRAK CHILLER (6) was enormous first-up at Tatura in a hot form race, beaten just a long neck after giving away a big start on the bend. A shade disappointing here at this trip subsequently but she is not a second-up performer. Watch for a far better effort today. FINANCE SHOGUN (1) has been easily accounted for in two runs this prep. Has been to the jump-outs since the last run which might bring him along. Worth another chance. STELLA CANTANTE (7) returns from an 18-week spell. Needs a mile to show her best but in a plain affair she is capable of sprinting well while fresh. LUNA FIELD (2) worked home evenly to be beaten under two lengths over 1150m at Nhill recently. Very fit now and Rawiller replacing a 3kg apprentice is a positive move. STEWART (11) backs up five days after a poor run at Yarra Valley. Might be a wet tracker only but can sneak into the frame for exotics punters.
